## Getting Started

### Code of Conduct

Before contributing to StreamPay™, please read and adhere to our [Code of Conduct](link-to-code-of-conduct.md). We prioritize creating a respectful and inclusive community for all contributors.

### How to Contribute

Contributions to StreamPay™ can take various forms, including:

- Code contributions
- Documentation improvements
- Bug reporting
- Feature requests
- Design enhancements
- Testing and quality assurance

If you're unsure where to start or have questions, feel free to reach out to our [community](#communication-channels).

### Development Environment

To set up your development environment for StreamPay™, refer to our [Development Environment Setup Guide](link-to-setup-guide.md). This guide provides step-by-step instructions for configuring your environment.

## Contributing

### Issue Tracking

We use [GitHub Issues](link-to-github-issues) to track tasks, bugs, and feature requests. You can find issues labeled as "beginner-friendly" or "help wanted" to get started.

### Submitting Changes

To contribute code or other changes, follow these steps:

1. Fork the StreamPay™ repository.
2. Create a new branch for your work.
3. Make your changes and commit them.
4. Push your changes to your fork.
5. Create a pull request (PR) from your fork's branch to the main StreamPay™ repository.

### Code Review

All contributions will undergo code review. Be prepared to address feedback and make necessary changes to your PR. Our maintainers will work with you to ensure your contribution aligns with our project's standards.

## Testing

### Testing Guidelines

We value thorough testing to maintain the quality of StreamPay™. Please follow our [Testing Guidelines](link-to-testing-guidelines.md) when submitting changes or new features. This helps us ensure reliable performance and functionality.

## Community

### Communication Channels

Join the StreamPay™ community on our [communication channels](link-to-community-channels) to connect with other contributors, ask questions, and share ideas.

### Feedback and Recognition

We appreciate your contributions! StreamPay™ acknowledges and recognizes contributors for their valuable input and effort. Your contributions help us achieve our goals, and we encourage your feedback on how we can improve further.

## License

By contributing to StreamPay™, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the project's [License](link-to-license.md).
